research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Seminole, TX, operates under a Home Rule form of government with a City Council and Mayor. Chet Clark serves as the Mayor. Rey Saldana is the Mayor Pro Tem and a Council Member for District 1, Place 1. Other identified council members and their designations include Dustin Wright (District 2, Place 2), Lloyd Glass (District 1, Place 2), Whitney Concotelli (District 3, Place 2), Blair Tharp (District 3, Place 1), and Landon Sims (District 2, Place 1). Some sources indicate five council members plus the mayor, while a detailed directory lists six council members including the Mayor Pro Tem.
